 **Definition and Calculation of the Median:**
A. It is a measure that refers to the middle value of a dataset when this dataset has been arranged in numerical order.
B. Given a specific set, the median is the value that corresponds to the middle value when this set has been sorted in ascending order.
C. Mathematically, it can be represented as the value that minimizes the sum of absolute differences between this value and the elements of the set. In formulas, it can be expressed as:
Median = $x_{min}(|x-x_i|)$,
where $x_i$ is an element within the range defined by the set. In the context of empirical probability distribution:
Median = $a_{min}(|a-a_i|)$,
where $a_i$ denotes an element of the range [n-1, n].

In simpler terms, the median is the middle number in a sorted, ascending or descending, list of numbers. If the set contains an even number of observations, the median is the average of the two middle numbers.

